HIVCAre Federated Analysis Documentation

Epidemiology and Inpatient Care Characteristics of HIV-positive Cancer Patients: Exploration of Real World Data from German University Hospitals

Bastian Reiter

2023-06-27

Objectives of descriptive analysis and data exploration

    1. Comparison of all subgroups
      • A1) Sample sizes and Demography (Sex, Age)
      • A2) Case count per patient
      • A3) Mean length of stay per patient
      • A4) Spatial distribution (Counts of patients from different postal code areas)
    1. HIVandCancer
      • B1) Primary cancer diagnosis subgroups and occurrence per year
      • B2) Age at admission separated for diagnosis subgroups and in 4-year time periods
    1. HIVandCancer vs. CancerOnly
      • C1) Age at presumed cancer onset
      • C2) Metastasis occurrence
      • C3) Time-to-event: Cancer onset to metastasis onset
      • C4) Count of distinct cancer entities
      • C5) Therapy modalities
      • C6) Count of chemotherapy sessions
      • C6) Discharge reasons (Death, Home)
      • C7) Occurrence of complications (ventilation, dialysis) after chemotherapy
      • C8) AIDS after chemotherapy
      • C9) Death after chemotherapy
    1. HIVandCancer vs. HIVOnly
      • D1) Age at presumed HIV onset
      • D2) AIDS occurrence
      • D3) Time-to-event: HIV onset to AIDS onset
    1. Sankey diagram: Sequence in presumed HIV / Cancer / Metastasis / AIDS onset
    1. Sankey diagram: Sequence of cancer therapy modalities

Objectives of inference analysis

** No explicit inference analysis goals **

Meta data description

Assumptions and definitions in analysis rational

General ICD coding

It is assumed that ICD Coding was performed abiding by established coding manuals (e.g. ZI HIV coding manual)

ICD cancer coding

The following ICD codes were used to identify patients presumed to have a cancerous disease in their history:

ICD-10 cancer codes used in analysis
ICD-10 codes Interpretation
Starting with C All malignant neoplasms (primary and secondary)
Starting with D0 In-situ neoplasms
D37 - D48 Neoplasms of uncertain / unknown behaviour
Z08 Follow-up examination after treatment for malignant neoplasms
Z85, Z92.6 Personal history of cancer / cancer therapy

ICD codes for metastases (C77, C78, C79) are not considered cancer codes and are treated separately.

Notes on inclusion of presumed cancer patients

In order to get a sufficient degree of integrity within the explored data, we include only patients for whom a cancer code with diagnosis type Hauptdiagnose is present. We consider the first occurrence of such a code within a patient’s documented history as the main cancer entity, that the respective patient is treated for. Furthermore, we refer to the admission date belonging to this code as the date of cancer onset.

Notes on presumption of AIDS manifestation

  • HIV code before or at the same time as AIDS defining code
  • Certain AIDS-defining cancer codes may occur ahead in time of HIV code occurrence. Patients in question would not be presumed to have AIDS.

Notes on concerns, limitations and potential bias sources

Concerns
Concern Estimated potential impact Comment
Disease onsets may be assumed wrongfully (as too late). Therefore, calculated onset intervals may be incorrect. Major
If a patient has more than one distinct cancer entity, therapy measures can not be linked to different entities. Major
Age at Admission not exact due to lack of exact birth date. Minor
Occurrence of implausible HIV coding. Minor
Postal code of patient taken from first admission, although moving between admissions is imaginable. Minor
